    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Updated again.\r\n\r\nChanges:\r\n- removed \"harvester-module\" internal default from HackyAIInfo.Modules, require modules to be explicitly listed in yaml instead\r\n- altered update rule to account for the above (tested and works as intended), which also makes it generally more \"fool-proof\", in particular if this and/or later *Module update rules are not run in the expected order\r\n\r\nI figured this is the better approach afterall, otherwise the update rules of later *Module PRs are going to be a royal pain to write, as we could never be 100% sure which modules have been added, are listed internally and so on.\r\nNot listing any internal defaults is much cleaner anyway."
